13 IC 24-4.5-1-302) IC 37-2-2-11) and with regulations adopted
14 under that act.
15 (8) The amount of interest.
16 (9) The amount of charge and principal due at maturity.
17 (10) A copy of sections 28, 28.5, and 30 of this chapter.
18 (11) The date of birth of the pledger.
19 (12) The type of government issued identification used to verify
20 the identity of the pledger, together with the name of the
21 governmental agency that issued the identification, and the
22 identification number present on the government issued
23 identification.
24 (13) The last date on which the pledged article or articles may be
