8 (3) "Debt" means liability on a claim.
9 (4) "Disposition" means a transfer, conveyance, or assignment of
10 property, including a change in the legal ownership of property
11 that occurs when a trustee is substituted for another trustee or
12 when at least one (1) trustee is added. The term also includes the
13 exercise of a power that causes a transfer of property to a trustee.
14 However, the term does not include the release or relinquishment
15 of an interest in property that, until the release or relinquishment,
16 was the subject of a qualified disposition.
17 (5) "Investment decision" means the retention, purchase, sale,
18 exchange, tender, or other transaction affecting the ownership of
19 or rights in an investment.
