113
1 (3) has been convicted of a felony under the laws of Indiana or
2 any other jurisdiction;
3 the director, subject to subsection (b), may issue and serve upon
4 the officer, director, or manager a notice of the director's intent to
5 issue an order removing the person from the person's office or
6 employment, an order prohibiting any participation by the person
7 in the conduct of the affairs of any creditor, or an order both
8 removing the person and prohibiting the person's participation.
9 (b) A violation, practice, or breach specified in subsection (a) is
10 subject to the authority of the director under subsections (a) and
11 (c) if the director finds any of the following:
12 (1) The interests of the creditor's customers could be seriously
