18 Sec. 10. "Consumer credit" means credit offered or extended to
19 a consumer primarily for a personal, family, or household purpose.
20 Sec. 10.5. "Consumer credit insurance" means insurance, other
21 than insurance on property, by which the satisfaction of debt in
22 whole or in part is a benefit provided, but does not include:
23 (1) insurance issued as an isolated transaction on the part of
24 the insurer not related to an agreement or plan for insuring
