160
1 (2) Charges for insurance as described in subsection (b).
2 (3) Notwithstanding provisions of the Consumer Credit
3 Protection Act (15 U.S.C. 1601 et seq.) concerning disclosure,
4 charges for other benefits, including insurance, conferred on
5 the consumer, if the benefits are of value to the consumer and
6 if the charges are reasonable in relation to the benefits, and
7 are excluded as permissible additional charges from the credit
8 service charge. With respect to any additional charge not
