6 commences with the date the loan is made. Differences in the
7 lengths of months are disregarded, and a day may be counted as
8 one-thirtieth (1/30) of a month. Subject to classifications and
9 differentiations the lender may reasonably establish, a part of a
10 month in excess of fifteen (15) days may be treated as a full month
11 if periods of fifteen (15) days or less are disregarded and if that
12 procedure is not consistently used to obtain a greater yield than
13 would otherwise be permitted. For purposes of computing average
14 daily balances, the creditor may elect to treat all months as
15 consisting of thirty (30) days.
