18 annual percentage rate on the amount of the refund required by
19 subsection (a) due at the time of prepayment or termination. The
20 director may impose an additional civil penalty of not greater than
21 one thousand dollars ($1,000) per occurrence if a creditor engages
22 in a pattern or practice of failing to comply with this subsection.
23 Sec. 7. If a creditor requires insurance, upon notice to the
24 creditor the debtor shall have the option of providing the required
25 insurance through an existing policy of insurance owned or
26 controlled by the debtor, or through a policy to be obtained and
27 paid for by the debtor, but the creditor may for reasonable cause
28 decline the insurance provided by the debtor.
29 Sec. 8. (a) A creditor may not contract for or receive a separate
30 charge for insurance in connection with a deferral (IC 37-2-3-7 or
31 IC 37-2-4-7), a refinancing (IC 37-2-3-8 or IC 37-2-4-8), or a
32 consolidation (IC 37-2-3-9 or IC 37-2-4-9), unless:
33 (1) the debtor agrees at or before the time of the deferral,
34 refinancing, or consolidation that the charge may be made;
35 (2) the debtor is or is to be provided with insurance for an
