234
1 except as follows:
2 (1) if the insurance relates to a revolving charge account or
3 revolving loan account, the term need extend only until the
4 payment of the debt under the account and may be sooner
5 terminated after at least thirty (30) days notice to the debtor;
6 or
7 (2) if the debtor is advised in writing that the insurance will be
8 written for a specified shorter time, the term need extend only
9 until the end of the specified time.
10 (c) The term of the insurance shall not extend more than fifteen
11 (15) days after the originally scheduled due date of the last
12 scheduled payment of the debt unless it is extended without
