33 Sec. 8. A person seeking to enforce section 7(c)(3), 7(c)(4), or
34 7(c)(5) of this chapter may not knowingly or intentionally
35 intimidate, coerce, or harass another person.
36 Sec. 9. It is unlawful for a creditor to discriminate against any
37 applicant with respect to any aspect of a credit transaction on the
